  "peopleAlsoAsk": [
    {
      "question": "How much should a full car detail cost?",
      "answer": "Full car detailing typically costs between $150-$500+ depending on vehicle size, condition, and services included. Basic packages start around $150-200, while premium packages with paint correction and ceramic coating can exceed $500-1000."
    },
    {
      "question": "How long does professional car detailing take?",
      "answer": "Professional car detailing takes 2-6 hours on average. Basic details take 2-3 hours, while full details with paint correction and ceramic coating can take 4-8 hours or multiple days."
    },
    {
      "question": "What is included in a full car detail?",
      "answer": "A full car detail includes exterior wash and wax, interior vacuum and shampoo, leather conditioning, window cleaning, wheel and tire cleaning, trim dressing, and often headlight restoration and engine bay cleaning."
    },
    {
      "question": "Is mobile car detailing worth it?",
      "answer": "Mobile car detailing is worth it for convenience, as the service comes to your location. It typically costs 10-20% more than shop detailing but saves time and travel. Quality is comparable to shop services."
    },
    {
      "question": "How often should I get my car detailed?",
      "answer": "Most experts recommend professional detailing 2-3 times per year, or every 4-6 months. Daily drivers in harsh conditions may benefit from quarterly detailing, while garage-kept vehicles can go 6-12 months between details."
    },
    {
      "question": "What is the difference between car wash and car detailing?",
      "answer": "Car washing is basic exterior cleaning, while detailing is comprehensive cleaning, restoration, and protection of both interior and exterior. Detailing includes paint correction, deep cleaning, and protective coatings."
    },
    {
      "question": "Does ceramic coating really work?",
      "answer": "Yes, ceramic coating provides long-lasting paint protection (3-5 years), enhanced gloss, easier cleaning, and protection from UV, chemicals, and minor scratches. It costs $500-2000+ but is more durable than wax."
    },
    {
      "question": "What is paint correction and do I need it?",
      "answer": "Paint correction removes swirl marks, scratches, and imperfections through polishing. It's needed before ceramic coating and recommended for vehicles with visible paint defects. Costs $500-1500 depending on severity."
    },
    {
      "question": "Can mobile detailing remove pet hair?",
      "answer": "Yes, professional mobile detailers can remove pet hair using specialized tools like rubber brushes, compressed air, and extraction equipment. This is often included in deep interior cleaning services."
    },
    {
      "question": "How do I prepare my car for mobile detailing?",
      "answer": "Remove personal items, empty trash, provide access to power/water within 100ft, unlock vehicle, and clear workspace around vehicle. Being present is optional but helpful for discussing specific concerns."
    },
    {
      "question": "Does car detailing remove scratches?",
      "answer": "Detailing can remove light surface scratches and swirl marks through paint correction/polishing. Deep scratches penetrating the clear coat require paint touch-up or professional body work."
    },
    {
      "question": "Is it better to detail a car before or after selling?",
      "answer": "Detailing before selling significantly increases perceived value and can add $500-2000 to sale price. Professional detailing costs $150-400 and provides excellent ROI when selling a vehicle."
    }
  ],

